description: The MetaGraph framework allows for indexing and analysis of very large biological sequence collections, producing compressed indexes that can represent several petabases of input data. The indexes can be efficiently queried with any query sequence of interest.
name: metagraph

owner.description: Bioconda is a distribution of bioinformatics software realized as a channel for the versatile Conda package manager.
owner.name: bioconda

summary: Ultra Scalable Framework for DNA Search, Alignment, Assembly.
